OL,3,CPolice heard Noah Donohoe had been
OL,4,Cacting 'strangely', inquest hears
OL,6,F"He said he was going to Cavehill with
OL,7,Fhis friends and his friends said that
OL,8,Fwas not the case."
OL,10,FMs Campbell asked if the investigation
OL,11,Fwas proceeding with the view that Noah
OL,12,Fhad lied.
OL,14,FMr Gardiner said "no, but it was
OL,15,Funusual".
OL,17,FThe jury at the inquest, which is now
OL,18,Fin its fifth week, were told that a
OL,19,Flater witness would help to look
OL,20,Ffurther into this matter.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@RO]vD@ROUwD@HO]
